n of tires for stockpiling:\nthe Erevan Tire Plant was making a shipment of tires for stockpiling that was twice as large as originally specified in November 1951.\n\nComment: The shortage of tires for current use is apparently being permitted to continue in order to accelerate both the stockpiling program and exports to Communist China. In 1951 the Erevan plant produced about 200,000 tires with tubes, approximately three percent of the total Soviet production.\n\nContinued shortages of tires since 1948 in the Soviet Union are essentially the result of limited manufacturing facilities rather than inadequate supplies of raw materials.\n\nFAR EAST\n\n5. Additional armor arrives in North Korea:\nthe arrival of additional tanks and self-propelled guns in the Pyongyang area. at least 43 tanks and 22 self-propelled artillery pieces have been brought into Korea on freight cars from China. The unidentified North Korean unit which originated these messages is to receive some of this armor.\n\nComment: Both the North Korean 105th Tank Division and 10th Mechanized Division are located in the Pyongyang area, and could reasonably be the recipient of these tanks", "token_count": 189, "token_end_0based": 188, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "soviet union 4 soviet plant doubles allocation of tires for stockpiling the erevan tire plant was making a shipment of tires for stockpiling that was twice as large as originally specified in november 1951 comment the shortage of tires for current use is apparently being permitted to continue in order to accelerate both the stockpiling program and exports to communist china in 1951 the erevan plant produced about 200 000 tires with tubes approximately three percent of the total soviet production continued shortages of tires since 1948 in the soviet union are essentially the result of limited manufacturing facilities rather than inadequate supplies of raw materials far east 5 additional armor arrives in north korea the arrival of additional tanks and self-propelled guns in the pyongyang area at least 43 tanks and 22 self-propelled artillery pieces have been brought into korea on freight cars from china the unidentified north korean unit which originated these messages is to receive some of this armor comment both the north korean 105th tank division and 10th mechanized division are located in the pyongyang area and could reasonably be the recipient of these tanks", "unred_source_page": 5}
